info.senderName: NWS Duluth (Northeast Minnesota and Northern Wisconsin)
info.headline: Winter Storm Warning issued March 10 at 2:16PM CST until March 12 at 6:00PM CST by NWS Duluth
info.description: ...WINTER STORM WARNING IN EFFECT FROM 6 AM CST SATURDAY TO 7 PM CDT SUNDAY... * WHAT...Heavy snow expected. Total snow accumulations of 5 to 9 inches. * WHERE...North St. Louis, Northern Cook and Lake, Central St. Louis and Pine Counties. This includes the Tribal Lands of the Mille Lacs Band, Lena Lake and, Hinckley areas and the Bois Forte Band, Lake Vermilion and, Nett Lake areas. * WHEN...From 6 AM CST Saturday to 7 PM CDT Sunday. * IMPACTS...Travel could be very difficult.
info.instruction: If you must travel, keep an extra flashlight, food, and water in your vehicle in case of an emergency. The latest road conditions can be obtained by calling 5 1 1. Road conditions can also be found at 511mn.org for Minnesota or 511wi.gov for Wisconsin.
